OL,3,CLabour would improve paternity leave
OL,4,Crights amid 'cultural shift' ` Rayner
OL,6,FA Labour government would enhance
OL,7,Fpaternity leave rights and seek a
OL,8,F"cultural shift" from employers to
OL,9,Fbetter support family life, the
OL,10,Fparty's deputy leader Angela Rayner
OL,11,Fhas said.
OL,13,FAhead of Father's Day, Labour have
OL,14,Fpledged to make parental leave a day
OL,15,Fone right for workers who start new
OL,16,Fjobs.
OL,18,FUnder the current rules, workers need
OL,19,Fto have had 26 weeks of continuous
OL,20,Femployment in a particular job before
OL,21,Fthey are entitled to paternity leave.
